				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Recycled Aggregate is a type of aggregate produced by crushing previously used concrete from sources like buildings, bridges, and roads. It is often used as a sub-base material for road construction, pathways, and hard-standing areas. Recycled aggregates have been increasingly considered for use in concrete due to the limited supply of natural aggregates and the corresponding carbon footprint. However, its use in concrete is often associated with lower performance due to physical properties.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">再生骨料是一种骨料，通过粉碎以前使用过的混凝土（如建筑物、桥梁和道路）而制成。它通常用作道路建设、人行道和硬地面的基层材料。由于天然骨料的供应有限以及相应的碳足迹，人们越来越多地考虑在混凝土中使用回收骨料。然而，由于物理性质的原因，在混凝土中使用再生骨料往往会降低其性能。</common:generalComment>
